div.p:
In the Case of a Witness: For what he says as a Witness,Witness, or
for what is said against him, to disable him from being a Witness,
or to take off his Credit, no Action of Slander will lie.

An Action upon the Case is there brought against the Defendants,
for maliciously causing the Plaintiff to be indicted of Treason;
upon which Indictment the Grand Jury found an Ignoramus.



And would be an occasion of multiplying Actions against the
Parties to the Suits, against Councel, the Attorneys, the Witnesses;
and so Suits would be infinite.
